Would be 5-star if:  (*1*) Data normalization: It seems like there is too much possible variation in user data being entered which makes it hard to identify accurate levels. Choose the standards and enforce them. (*2*) Allow multi-field search: When I tried searching with title and author, it would just ignore title and only give author. Why not provide a way to search by both. (*3*) Scan-to-title-search: Scanner usually found books with no helpful information (no reading levels entered), but if I searched by title I would find a list of 3-5 entries for that book (maybe different printing, but same book reading level). You could improve user experience by maybe adding a way to link to title/author search from the scanner result..."Not the right book? Search by title" and it would auto-populate the title search field. Might not always work but it's a start. (*4*) Allow user to edit search after they get results. The results sometimes need find-tuning but when I click "back" on my phone it takes me back to a blank form, why not cache those search fields or at least put an "edit/filter search" link in results to narrow results without totally reentering all the info every time.
Scanner is a bit wobbly. Ended up manually entering majority of info because Sakura something is default. Not worth the effort.

I also love the manual entry option.  Would be easier to use on a computer but it found many books that didn't have a bar code to scan.  Would definitely recommend, just understand that no app will find all  of your books.

replyContent: Hi Kellie, we released an update yesterday to resolve the issue with manual searching on your device.  Please let us know if this worked for you.  We apologize for the delay in adding a solution for your Samsung Stratosphere phone.  Thanks!

replyContent: Hi GooglesOfEscape, we apologize you are experiencing issues with the licensing check.  We use the standard GooglePlay verification system that validates copies of our app that were downloaded from the Play store.  Do you have an active internet connection when experiencing this issue?  Thanks!
